http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Brahmasthana-temple-fete/article14006238.ece

Hundreds of devotees thronged the Brahmasthana temple at Kondungallur to have a dharsan of Mata Amrithanandamayi on Monday. Special pujas, meditation, discourse and bhajans were conducted as part of the festival. Many people, including T.N. Prathapan, MLA, BJP State general secretary Sobha Surendran; Thrissur Range IG M.R. Ajithkumar visited the spiritual leader. “Our country has two faces. If one is of developmental of science information technology, the other is of poverty, violence against woman, and illiteracy. This situation should change,” the Mata said. The festival will conclude on Tuesday.